{"BR": {"BR_id": "3671", "BR_author": "IamRavikantSingh", "BRopenT": "2020-06-05T17:31:25Z", "BRcloseT": "2020-06-06T05:29:34Z", "BR_text": {"BRsummary": "FV cipher-text data change during decryption.", "BRdescription": "\n <denchmark-h:h2>Description</denchmark-h>\n \n During the decryption process, the ciphertext was soft copied and it changed the ciphertext value during decryption. So we lose the value of ciphertext.\n <denchmark-h:h2>How to Reproduce</denchmark-h>\n \n \n Create a ciphertext\n Decrypt that ciphertext\n Retry to decrypt the same ciphertext (wrong result)\n \n \t"}, "comments": {"comments_0": {"comment_id": 1, "comment_author": "IamRavikantSingh", "commentT": "2020-06-05T17:57:28Z", "comment_text": "\n \t\tThis issue was not caught by earlier tests because for every test of encryption-decryption process new parameters were generated and every ciphertext was tested for correct values only ones\n \t\t"}}}, "commit": {"commit_id": "27c6799a2bdde2a27023bf07e29c34f50ff33995", "commit_author": "Ravikant Singh", "commitT": "2020-06-06 06:29:33+01:00", "commit_complexity": {"commit_NLOC": "1.0", "commit_CCN": "1.0", "commit_Nprams": "1.0"}, "changed_files": {"file_0": {"file_change_type": "MODIFY", "file_Nmethod": 1, "file_old_name": "syft\\frameworks\\torch\\he\\fv\\decryptor.py", "file_new_name": "syft\\frameworks\\torch\\he\\fv\\decryptor.py", "file_complexity": {"file_NLOC": "43", "file_CCN": "9", "file_NToken": "358"}, "hunks": {"hunk_0": {"Ismethod": 1, "added_lines": "36", "deleted_lines": "35", "method_info": {"method_name": "decrypt", "method_params": "self,encrypted", "method_startline": "25", "method_endline": "43", "method_complexity": {"method_NLOC": "5", "method_CCN": "1", "method_NToken": "50", "method_nesting_level": "1"}}}}}, "file_1": {"file_change_type": "MODIFY", "file_Nmethod": 1, "file_old_name": "test\\torch\\tensors\\test_fv.py", "file_new_name": "test\\torch\\tensors\\test_fv.py", "file_complexity": {"file_NLOC": "331", "file_CCN"